# agent-pods worker color palette — SINGLE SOURCE OF TRUTH.
# One "<tmux-color-code> <name>" per line. Read by bin/pod-add-worker (bash) and
# modules/mcp/pod_manager_server.py (python). Keep them from drifting apart by
# reading THIS file in both, never re-listing the colors inline.
#
# HARD RULE (the black-on-black bug): every code here must be a DARK jewel tone so a
# light foreground (fg=colour231) stays readable on it. A window's body bg is set to
# this code paired with fg=colour231 in pod-add-worker; a bare bg with no light fg is
# exactly the black-on-black regression. Do not add a light/saturated code here.
#
# Lines starting with '#' and blank lines are ignored. Order = assignment preference.
colour18 ocean
colour52 maroon
colour22 forest
colour58 olive
colour53 purple
colour23 teal
colour60 slate
colour94 rust
